      <div class="section">
        <h2>How Long Should You Track?</h2>
        <p>You don't need to track protein every day forever. The goal is calibration, not permanent logging. Most men need two to four weeks of consistent daily tracking to develop accurate intuition about their intake. After that, you know what a 35-gram breakfast looks like without logging it.</p>
        <p>At that point, shift to periodic check-ins — a week every couple of months to recalibrate, or whenever your diet changes significantly. Some people find daily tracking becomes genuinely effortless after the first month — 30 seconds, three times a day, no friction. If it stops feeling like work, there's no reason to stop.</p>

